      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fultonville%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "Founded in the early 19th century, Fultonville grew around the Erie Canal, becoming a bustling trade hub for steamboats and freight.",
